comments.body:
Hi ,Thanks for your concern .  I can't reproduce it .Could you please share with us your Xcode , CLI and TiSDK version ?
Run this command: *appc ti info -t ios*
 If no issues detected, Manually launch the iOS Simulator, then from the iOS Simulator menu, select "Reset Content and Settings"
I recommend you to clean and build apps using command:
> *appc run*
> iOS
